cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the use of deep learning techniques for mapping winter vegetation quality coverage using multi-temporal SAR Sentinel-1 data. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis and classification. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of SAR data for vegetation mapping also falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of different machine learning algorithms, which falls under the domain of neural networks (cs.NE).
